The paper discusses the use of model-driven development and component-based software development for building self-adaptive software systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) and software design (cs.SD) categories. The paper also mentions context-oriented software, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the need for adaptability in highly dynamic environments, which is related to distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
